Race.SpecificTitle: PW Fantasy Sports -- Authorize Fantasy Sports Contests - Act 322, 2018
Race.SummaryText: PROPOSITION TO AUTHORIZE FANTASY SPORTS CONTESTS.
Race.FullText: Shall fantasy sports contests be permitted in the parish of Catahoula?

Race.SpecificTitle: PW Prop. No. 1 of 2 -- 8.36 Mills Continuation - PJ - 10 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of Catahoula, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), levy and collect a tax of eight and thirty-six hundredths (8.36) mills on all the property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $334,400 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2020 and ending with the year 2029, for the purpose of acquiring, constructing, improving, maintaining, operating and/or supporting the Catahoula Parish Library and its branches, including purchasing books and equipment therefor, said millage to represent an eight hundredths of a mill (.08) increase (due to reappraisal) over the 8.28 mills tax authorized to be levied through the year 2019 pursuant to an election held on October 17, 2009?

Race.SpecificTitle: PW Prop. No. 2 of 2 -- 2.07 Mills Rededication - PJ - 5 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of Catahoula, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), be authorized to rededicate the proceeds heretofore and hereafter received from the levy of a special tax of two and seven hundredths (2.07) mills authorized to be levied through the year 2019 for the purpose of acquiring, constructing, improving, maintaining and/or operating the public health units of the Parish at an election held on October 17, 2009 on all the property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $82,800 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), such that tax proceeds determined by the governing authority of the Parish to be surplus to public health unit needs shall be used for solid waste collection and disposal and sanitation purposes (except $200,000 of proceeds heretofore collected shall be used for public health unit purposes) and shall the levy of the tax be extended for a period of five (5) years through the year 2024?

Race.SpecificTitle: Larto-Mayna Recreation Dist. -- 5.20 Mills Renewal - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall Larto-Mayna Recreation District of the Parish of Catahoula, State of Louisiana (the "District"), levy a special tax of five and twenty hundredths (5.20) mills on all the property subject to taxation in the District (an estimated $26,930 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2020 and ending with the year 2029, for the purpose of acquiring, constructing, improving, maintaining and/or operating recreational facilities of the District?

Race.SpecificTitle: Fire Protection Dist. No. 4 -- $30 Parcel Fee Continuation - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Fire Protection District No. 4 Proposition
(Parcel Fee Continuation)
Race.FullText: Shall Fire Protection District No. 4 of the Parish of Catahoula, State of Louisiana (the "District"), continue to levy and collect an annual parcel fee of Thirty Dollars ($30) on each lot, subdivided portion of ground or individual tract upon which is located, either in whole or in part, a residential or commercial structure, regardless of the structure's being occupied or unoccupied, for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2018 and ending with the year 2027 (an estimated $21,090 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of said parcel fee for an entire year), for the purpose of acquiring, constructing, maintaining and operating fire protection facilities and equipment, including paying the cost of obtaining water for fire protection purposes and salaries of firemen, and all purposes incidental thereto?
